“’Ů@ce656880e604612955005955306dc5819fbbe8105d83d28f2def80da052fafdbÚTitle: This week in Nushell #243
Path: Nushell
Content:
devyn made lots of improvements, mostly around plugin support: 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12580] switched the plugin msgpack protocol to named format
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12575] fixed the error output in the Python plugin to match LabeledError
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12574] added an example Nushell plugin written in Nushell itself
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12550] improved safety of 
``get_unchecked_str``
 in 
``nu_system::macos``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12549] replaced subtraction of Instants and Durations with saturating subtractions
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12533] removed unnecessary fields from Python plugin signature
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12526] added a panic unwind handler during plugin calls
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12510] improved error messages for plugin protocol by removing 
``#[serde(untagged)]``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12448] introduced local socket mode and foreground terminal control for plugins
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12305] implemented copy-on-write for record values
ayax79 did lots of work on dataframe support: 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12577] removed the polars dtypes command
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12571] only marked collected dataframes as from_lazy=false when collect is called from the collect command
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12554] upgraded nu-cmd-dataframe to polars 0.39
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12551] upgraded nu_plugin_polars to polars 0.39.1
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12538] fixed NuLazyFrame/NuDataFrame conversion issues
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12528] cleaned up to_pipe_line_data and cache_and_to_value, making them part of CustomValueSupport
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12525] ensured that lazy frames converted via to-lazy are not converted back to eager frames later in the pipeline
poliorcetics 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12593] added more details to 
``version``
amtoine 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12591] added "to nuon" enumeration of possible styles
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12553] created a new 
``nuon``
 crate from 
``from nuon``
 and 
``to nuon``
fdncred 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12589] improved 
``nu --lsp``
 command tooltips
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12564] added the ability to set metadata
WindSoilder 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12573] set the type of default NU_LIB_DIRS and NU_PLUGIN_DIRS to 
``list<string>``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12559] disallowed skip on external stream
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12534] removed useless path.rs
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12531] unified 
``working_set.error``
 usage
TheLostLambda 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12569] fixed shell_integration to set window title on startup
IanManske 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12568] boxed 
``ImportPattern``
 in 
``Expr``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12529] added 
``ListItem``
 type for 
``Expr::List``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12508] made 
``group-by``
 return errors in closure
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12324] added 
``Record::into_columns``
sholderbach 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12566] updated crate feature flags
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12542] implemented 
``FusedIterator``
 for record iterators
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12540] did minor housekeeping in the parser
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12523] improved 
``with-env``
 robustness
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12522] disallowed setting the 
``PWD``
 via 
``load-env``
 input
merelymyself 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12517] used abbreviated string instead of debug string for 
``DatetimeParseError``
s
schrieveslaach 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12454] improved config behaviour in LSP Mode
YizhePKU 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12262] fixed circular source causing Nushell to crash
’Ů@07423ebb0521c99e4f9bc6a7b6237d09eda2fe7e5721194c7d8b4cc1371a7d81Ú5Title: This week in Nushell #243
Path: Documentation
Content:
SCKelemen 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1356] fixed(lang-guide): IEE-754 -> IEEE-754
maxim-uvarov 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1355] added the 
``not``
 operator in the list of the order of operations
devyn 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1353] documented all variants of 
``Value``
 and fixed error types
hustcer 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1351] upgraded all actions for GitHub workflows
’Ů@3fea94548bf5f274b98afafbc2972c679815fdbca02b7e53c39f30e03fb72b0eÚěTitle: This week in Nushell #243
Path: Nu_Scripts
Content:
devyn 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nu_scripts/pull/822] added nu_plugin_nu_example to bump-version.nu
nils-degroot 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nu_scripts/pull/821] added 
``zellij action new-tab``
 completions
kubouch 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nu_scripts/pull/820] reverted "fix: prefix conda commands with 
``conda``
"
zhangymPerson 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nu_scripts/pull/819] added mvn completion
